RegionLength.name: Descriptor region length
RegionLength.help_text: If non-zero, specifies the length of the Descriptor region.

NumComponents.name: Number of Flash Components
NumComponents.help_text: Specifies the number of Flash components that will be installed on the target machine. Valid values are 0,1,2 - 0 causes only ME region to be built.

ComponentBaseAddr.name: Component Base Address
ComponentBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Component portion of the Flash Descriptor.

RegionBaseAddr.name: Region base address
RegionBaseAddr.help_text: Flash Region Base Address (FRBA). This identifies address bits [11:4] for the Region portion of the Flash Descriptor. Bits [24:12] and bits [3:0] are 0.

MasterBaseAddr.name: Master base address
MasterBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the Master portion of the Flash Descriptor.

PchStrapLength.name: Number of PCH straps
PchStrapLength.help_text: PCH Strap Length (PSL). Identifies the 1s based number of Dwords of PCH Straps to be read, up to 255 DWs (1KB) max. A setting of all 0's indicates there are no PCH DW straps.

PchBaseAddr.name: PCH straps base address
PchBaseAddr.help_text: Flash PCH Strap Base Address (FPSBA). This identifies address bits [11:4] for the PCH Strap portion of the Flash Descriptor. Bits [24:12] and bits [3:0] are 0. For validation purposes, the recommended FISBA is 0x10.

ProcStrapLength.name: Number of PROC straps
ProcStrapLength.help_text: The number of PROC straps to be read. Valid values are 0 to 1.

ProcBaseAddr.name: PROC straps base address
ProcBaseAddr.help_text: Flash Master Base Address (FMBA). This identifies address bits [11:4] for the Master portion of the Flash Descriptor. Bits [24:12] and bits [3:0] are 0. A recommended FMBA is 20h.

RegInitBaseAddr.name: Register Init Base Address
RegInitBaseAddr.help_text: Identifies address bits [11:4] for the DMI Register Init portion of the Flash Descriptor.

RegInitLength.name: Register Init Length
RegInitLength.help_text: 1's based number of DMI Register Init entries. Each entry is two DWORDS.

ReadStatusFreq.name: Read ID and Read Status clock frequency
ReadStatusFreq.help_text: If more that one Flash component exists, this field must be the lowest common frequency of the different components.

WriteEraseFreq.name: Write and erase clock frequency
WriteEraseFreq.help_text: If more that one Flash component exists, this field must be the lowest common frequency of the different components.

FastReadFreq.name: Fast read clock frequency
FastReadFreq.help_text: This field is undefined if the Fast Read Support is set to false.

DensityComp1.name: Flash component 1 density
DensityComp1.help_text: This field identifies the size of the 1st Flash component.

DensityComp2.name: Flash component 2 density
DensityComp2.help_text: This field identifies the size of the 2nd Flash component.

DualOutputFastReadSupport.name: Dual Output Fast Read Support
DualOutputFastReadSupport.help_text: false: Not Supported. true: Dual Output Fast Read instruction is issued in all cases where the the Fast Read would have been issued.

InvalidInst0.name: Invalid Instruction 0
InvalidInst0.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst1.name: Invalid Instruction 1
InvalidInst1.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst2.name: Invalid Instruction 2
InvalidInst2.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst3.name: Invalid Instruction 3
InvalidInst3.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst4.name: Invalid Instruction 4
InvalidInst4.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst5.name: Invalid Instruction 5
InvalidInst5.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst6.name: Invalid Instruction 6
InvalidInst6.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

InvalidInst7.name: Invalid Instruction 7
InvalidInst7.help_text: Op-code for an invalid instruction that the Flash Controller should protect against chip erase. This byte should be set to 0 if there is no instruction to protect against.

ReadAccess.name: Read Access
ReadAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x0B = Production, 0x1B = Production w/ access to PDR (should ONLY be used if PDR region is implemented). Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, read access is granted.

WriteAccess.name: Write Access
WriteAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x0A = Production, 0x1A = Production w/ access to PDR (should ONLY be used if PDR region is implemented). Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, write access is granted.

ReadAccess.name: Read Access
ReadAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x0D = Production. Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, read access is granted.

WriteAccess.name: Write Access
WriteAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x0C = Production. Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, write access is granted.

ReadAccess.name: Read Access
ReadAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x08 = Production. Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, read access is granted.

WriteAccess.name: Write Access
WriteAccess.help_text: 0xFF = Debug/Manufacturing, 0x08 = Production. Each bit corresponds to Regions [7:0]. If the bit is set, write access is granted.

DmiReqIdDisable.name: DMI RequesterID Check Disable
DmiReqIdDisable.help_text: The purpose is to support server environments with multiple processors where each have a different RequesterID that can each access the flash. false = DMI RequesterID Checks are enabled. true = DMI RequesterID Checks are disabled.

MacSecDisable.name: MACsec Disable
MacSecDisable.help_text: MACsec is a hop-by-hop network security solution. It provides Layer 2 encryption and authenticity/integrity protection for packets traveling between MACsec-enabled nodes of the network.

LanPhyPowerControl.value: GPIO12 is used in native mode as LANPHYPC
LanPhyPowerControl.value_list: GPIO12 is used in native mode as LANPHYPC,,GPIO12 default is General Purpose (GP) output
LanPhyPowerControl.name: LAN PHY Power Control GPIO12 Select

SmBusEnable.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus Enable
SmBusEnable.help_text: Configures if Intel (R) ME SMBus is enabled.

TpmClockFrequency.name: TPM Clock Frequency
TpmClockFrequency.help_text: This field identifies the frequency that should be used with the TPM on SPI. This field is undefined if the TPM on SPI is disabled by softstrap.

DualOutputReadEnable.name: Dual Output Read Enable
DualOutputReadEnable.help_text: This soft strap only has effect if Dual Output read is discovered as supported vis the SFDP. If parameter table is not detected via SFDP, this bit has no effect and Dual Output Read is controlled via the Flash Descriptor Component Section. Dual Output Fast Read Support Bit.

DualIoReadEnable.name: Dual IO Read Enable
DualIoReadEnable.help_text: This soft strap only has effect if Dual I/O Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

QuadOutputReadEnable.name: Quad Output Read Enable
QuadOutputReadEnable.help_text: This soft strap only has effect if Quad Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

QuadIoReadEnable.name: Quad IO Read Enable
QuadIoReadEnable.help_text: This soft strap only has effect if Quad Output Read is discovered as supported via the SFDP.

SmBusI2cAddrEn.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus I2C Address Enable
SmBusI2cAddrEn.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus I2C Target Address Enabled

SmBusI2cAddr.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus I2C Address
SmBusI2cAddr.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus I2C Target Address (this is for testing purposes)

SmBusMctpAddrEn.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus MCTP Address Enable
SmBusMctpAddrEn.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus MCTP Target Address Enabled

SmBusMctpAddr.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus MCTP Address
SmBusMctpAddr.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus MCTP Target Address

SmBusAsdAddrEn.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus ASD Address Enable
SmBusAsdAddrEn.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus ASD Target Address Enabled

SmBusAsdAddr.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus ASD Address
SmBusAsdAddr.help_text: Intel (R) ME SMBus ASD Target Address

GbePhySmBusAddr.name: GbE PHY SMBus Address
GbePhySmBusAddr.help_text: If bit 0 set, OEM programmed SmBus address is assigned to GbE PHY by chipset. This strap must be made available to ME & PMC.

GbeSmBusAddr.name: GbE MAC SMBus Address
GbeSmBusAddr.help_text: This is the SMBus address used by SMT to accept SMBus cycles from the PHY. This must be provided to SMT1,2,3 and GbE This strap must be backed in the RTC well. The recommended flash value for this field is: 1110000b

PhyConnectivity.value_list: 00: No PHY connected,,01: PHY on SMBus (use SMT1),,10: PHY on SMLink0,,11: PHY on SMLink2 (use SMT3)
PhyConnectivity.name: PHY Connectivity
PhyConnectivity.help_text: Defines if PHY is connected to Intel (R) SMBus 2 segment or not.

Smt1SubVidDid4ASF.name: Intel (R) ME SMBus Subsystem Vendor & Device ID for ASF
Smt1SubVidDid4ASF.help_text: [15:0]-Subsystem Vendor ID, [31:16]-Subsystem Device ID. The values are provided as bytes 8-9 and 10-11 of the data payload to an external master when it initiates a Directed GET UDID Block Read Command to the Intel (R) ME SMBus controller's ASF2 address

TempAlertSml1AlertSel.name: TEMP_ALERT# or SML1ALERT# Select
TempAlertSml1AlertSel.help_text: This strap determines the native mode operation of GPIO73.

SubtractDecodeAgentEn.name: Subtractive Decode Agent Enable
SubtractDecodeAgentEn.help_text: Set this bit to 'true' if there is a PCI bridge chip connnected to the PCH, that requires subtractive decode agent. Set to 'false' if the platform has no PCI bridge chip.

GbeOverPcieEn.name: Intel (R) PHY Over PCI Express Enable
GbeOverPcieEn.help_text: false: GbE MAC/PHY comm. is not enabled over PCIe. true: The port selected by GBE PCIe Port Select is used for GbE MAC/PHY over PCIe comm.

GbePciePortSelect.value_list: 000: Port 3,,001: Port 4,,010: Port 5 Lane 0,,011: Port 5 Lane 1,,100: Port 5 Lane 2,,101: Port 5 Lane 3
GbePciePortSelect.name: GbE PCIe Port Select
GbePciePortSelect.help_text: Sets the default value of the RPC.GBEPCIERPSEL register which is used to determine which PCIe port to use for GbE MAC/PHY over PCI Express communication.

PCIeLaneReversal2.name: PCIe Lane Reversal 2
PCIeLaneReversal2.help_text: Sets the default value for the PCIe Port 5, Device 28 Function 4Lane Reversal register.

PCIeLaneReversal1.name: PCIe Lane Reversal 1
PCIeLaneReversal1.help_text: Sets the default value for the PCIe Port 1, Device 28 Function 0, Lane Reversal register.

PCIePortConf1.value_list: 00: 4x1 Ports 1-4 (x1),,01: 1x2, 2x1 Port 1 (x2), Port 2 (disabled), Ports 3, 4 (x1),,10: 2x2 Port 1 (x2), Port 3 (x2), Ports 2, 4 (disabled),,11: 1x4 Port 1 (x4), Ports 2-4 (disabled)
PCIePortConf1.name: PCIe Port Configuration Strap 1
PCIePortConf1.help_text: These straps set the default value of the PCI Express Port Configuration 1 register covering PCIe ports 1-4.

Usb3Port3PciePort1Mode.value: PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to USB3 Port 3
Usb3Port3PciePort1Mode.value_list: PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE),,PCIe Lane 1 is statically assigned to USB3 Port 3
Usb3Port3PciePort1Mode.name: USB3 Port 3 PCIe Port 1 Mode
Usb3Port3PciePort1Mode.help_text: This soft strap sets the default value of the USB3 PCI Express Port1 Mode register that resides in the core well.

Usb3Port4PciePort2Mode.value: PCIe Lane 2 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE)
Usb3Port4PciePort2Mode.value_list: PCIe Lane 2 is statically assigned to PCI Express (or GbE),,PCIe Lane 2 is statically assigned to USB3 Port 4
Usb3Port4PciePort2Mode.name: USB3 Port 4 PCIe Port 2 Mode
Usb3Port4PciePort2Mode.help_text: This soft strap sets the default value of the USB3 PCI Express Port2 Mode register that resides in the core well.

MeBootFromFlash.name: ME boot from Flash
MeBootFromFlash.help_text: If true, ME will boot directly from Flash.

Reserved.name: Reserved
Reserved.help_text: Intel Reserved. This is an unsupported setting and must be set to false.

MeDbgSmbusEmergencyModeEn.name: ME Debug SMBus Emergency Mode Enable
MeDbgSmbusEmergencyModeEn.help_text: ME Debug SMBus Emergency Mode Help.

MeDbgSmbusEmergencyModeAddr.name: ME Debug SMBus Emergency Mode Address
MeDbgSmbusEmergencyModeAddr.help_text: '0' : the default address, 38h, is used for MDES writes non-zero : specifies the SMBus address used for MDES writes.

MeDbgLanEmergencyModeEn.name: ME Debug LAN Emergency Mode
MeDbgLanEmergencyModeEn.help_text: This bit should be set to 'true' if it is desired to capture events with the ME Debug tool. This bit should be set to 'false' for production platforms.

MeDebugExtendedDataEnable.value_list: Disabled (default),,MDES data transmitted over SMBUS by boot path (including ROM)
MeDebugExtendedDataEnable.name: ME Debug Extended Data Enable

MeResetCapture.name: ME Reset Capture on CLR_RST1#
MeResetCapture.help_text: true = ME will assert at the CL_RST1# when it resets. false = ME does not assert.

DeepSx.name: Deep SX Enable
DeepSx.help_text: Deep SX refers to the low power states designated Deep S3, Deep S4, and Deep S5.

FtpmStrapDisable.name: Intel (R) Platform Trust Technology Permanent Disable
FtpmStrapDisable.help_text: Yes: PTT disabled. No: PTT enabled.

PCIeLaneReversal3.value: PCIe Port 6 Lane 0-3 are not reversed
PCIeLaneReversal3.value_list: PCIe Port 6 Lane 0-3 are not reversed,,PCIe Port 6 Lane 0-3 are reversed when Port 6 is configured as 1x4
PCIeLaneReversal3.name: PCIe Lane Reversal 3
PCIeLaneReversal3.help_text: Bit lane reversal behavior for PCIe Port 6 if configured as a x4 PCIe port.

PciePortConfigStrap3.name: PCIe Port Configuration Strap 3
PciePortConfigStrap3.help_text: Set the default value of the PCI Express port Configuration 2 register covering PCIe port 6.

PciePortConfigStrap2.name: PCIe Port Configuration Strap 2
PciePortConfigStrap2.help_text: Set the default value of the PCI Express port Configuration 2 register covering PCIe port 5.

Sata0PcieP6L3Mode.value_list: Statically assigned to SATA Port 0,,Statically assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 3,,Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO34 pin
Sata0PcieP6L3Mode.name: SATA Port 0 PCIe Port 6 Lane 3 Mode
Sata0PcieP6L3Mode.help_text: Set SATA Port 0 PCIe Port 6 Lane 3 Mode. If the native mode of GIPO34 pin is a '1', then it is assigned to SATA Port 0, else it is assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 3.

Sata1PcieP6L2Mode.value_list: Statically assigned to SATA Port 1,,Statically assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 2,,Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO35 pin
Sata1PcieP6L2Mode.name: SATA Port 1 PCIe Port 6 Lane 2 Mode
Sata1PcieP6L2Mode.help_text: Set SATA Port 1 PCIe Port 6 Lane 2 Mode. If the native mode of GIPO35 pin is a '1', then it is assigned to SATA Port 1, else it is assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 2.

Sata2PcieP6L1Mode.value_list: Statically assigned to SATA Port 2,,Statically assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 1,,Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO36 pin
Sata2PcieP6L1Mode.name: SATA Port 2 PCIe Port 6 Lane 1 Mode
Sata2PcieP6L1Mode.help_text: Set SATA Port 2 PCIe Port 6 Lane 1 Mode. If the native mode of GIPO36 pin is a '1', then it is assigned to SATA Port 2, else it is assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 1.

Sata3PcieP6L0Mode.value_list: Statically assigned to SATA Port 3,,Statically assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 0,,Assigned based on the native mode of GPIO37 pin
Sata3PcieP6L0Mode.name: SATA Port 3 PCIe Port 6 Lane 0 Mode
Sata3PcieP6L0Mode.help_text: Set SATA Port 3 PCIe Port 6 Lane 0 Mode. If the native mode of GIPO37 pin is a '1', then it is assigned to SATA Port 3, else it is assigned to PCIe Port 6 Lane 0.

BackboneClkSrcSelect.value_list: OPI PLL is the source,,PCIe PLL is the source
BackboneClkSrcSelect.name: Backbone Clock Source Select

PcieNandSelect.value: NAND Cycle Router configured for PCIe NAND x2
PcieNandSelect.value_list: NAND Cycle Router configured for PCIe NAND x1,,NAND Cycle Router configured for PCIe NAND x2
PcieNandSelect.name: PCIe NAND x1 or x2 Select
PcieNandSelect.help_text: Select NAND cycle Router configuration for PCIe

T205bTimer.value_list: t205b timer is disabled,,PCH will count 99ms from PWROK assertion before PLTRST# is de-asserted
T205bTimer.name: PCIe Power Stable Timer Enable
T205bTimer.help_text: Platform is required to ensure timing of PWROK and SYS_PWROK in such a way that it satisfies the PCIe timing requirement of power stable to reset de-assertion.

SlpWlanGpio29Sel.name: SLP_WLAN# or GPIO29 Select
SlpWlanGpio29Sel.help_text: false = GPIO29 can only be used as SLP_WLAN#. true = GPIO29 is available for GPIO configuration

T1001Timing.name: t1001 Timing
T1001Timing.help_text: t1001 timing is the min timing from CPUPWRGD assertion to SUS_STAT#

T573Timing.name: t573 Timing
T573Timing.help_text: t573 timing is the min timing from XCK_PLL locked to CPUPWRGD high

IcBtSoftStrp.value_list: Full Clock Integrated Mode,,Buffered Through Mode
IcBtSoftStrp.name: BTM/FCIM Select
IcBtSoftStrp.help_text: If PCH clock boot mode is specified by this soft strap, then this parameter specifies whether PCH clocks boot in FCIM or BTM.

InputFile.name: OEM Section Binary input file
InputFile.help_text: The contents of this file (up to 256 bytes) are copied directly into the OEM section of the Flash Descriptor.

RegionLength.name: BIOS region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the BIOS region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: BIOS binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the BIOS image binary that will be copied into this region.

RegionLength.name: GbE LAN region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the GbE LAN region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: GbE binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the Gbe image binary that will be copied into this region.

LANEn.name: Intel (R) Integrated LAN Enable
LANEn.help_text: Intel (R) Integrated LAN related PCH Straps are set up automatically according to this setting.

RegionLength.name: PDR region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the PDR region in bytes. Set this to zero and specify an input file if you want the tool to determine the appropriate size for the region.

InputFile.name: PDR binary input file
InputFile.help_text: This is the PDR image binary that will be copied into this region.

RegionLength.name: ME region length
RegionLength.help_text: This is the size of the ME region in bytes. Set this to 0 to make the region length equal to the binary file length (rounded up to 4k). Extra space will be filled with 0xFF.

InputFile.name: ME Binary Input File
InputFile.help_text: This is the path to a binary file that will be used for the ME region.

WcodChosen.name: WCOD Id
WcodChosen.help_text: Determines which wireless LAN micro code will be supported in the firmware image

LoclChosen.value_list: 0x02 FR,,0x03 GER,,0x04 CH,,0x05 JPN,,0x06 RUS,,0x07 ITA,,0x08 ESP,,0x09 PTB,,0x0A KOR,,0x0B CHS,,0x0C ARA,,0x0D CZE,,0x0E DAN,,0x0F GRE,,0x10 FIN,,0x11 HEB,,0x12 HUN,,0x13 DUT,,0x14 NOR,,0x15 POL,,0x16 POR,,0x17 SLK,,0x18 SLV,,0x19 SWE,,0x1A THA,,0x1B TUR,,0x01 EN
LoclChosen.name: LOCL Id
LoclChosen.help_text: Determines which localized language data will be used by the firmware for the secure output screens (Examples: SOL / KVM)

FwuOemId.name: FW Update OEM ID
FwuOemId.help_text: Enter UUID or file containing the UUID. This UUID will make sure that customers can only update a platform with an image coming from the OEM of the platform. If set to zero than any input is valid (including none) when doing a FW update.

LanPowerWell.name: LAN Power Well Config
LanPowerWell.help_text: 0 = Core Well, 1 = Sus Well, 2 = ME Well, 3 = SLP_LAN# (MGPIO3)

WlanPowerWell.name: WLAN Power Well Config
WlanPowerWell.help_text: 0x80 = Disabled, 0x82 = Sus Well, 0x83 = ME Well, 0x84 = WLAN Power Controlled via SLP_M# || SPDA, 0x86 = WLAN Sleep via SLP_WLAN#

HostMeRegUnlock.name: Host ME Region Flash Protection Override
HostMeRegUnlock.help_text: Set this to TRUE if you want the ability to have BIOS write to the ME Region. Set to FALSE to opt out.

ProcMissing.value_list: No onboard glue logic,,Glue logic tied to GPIO24
ProcMissing.name: PROC_MISSING
ProcMissing.help_text: This value will determine if there is glue logic present on the platform to detect a missing processor on desktop platforms.

ProcEmulation.value_list: No Emulation,,EMULATE Intel (R) vPro (TM) capable Processor,,EMULATE Intel (R) Core (TM) branded Processor,,EMULATE Intel (R) Celeron (R) branded Processor,,EMULATE Intel (R) Pentium (R) branded Processor,,EMULATE Intel (R) Xeon (R) branded Processor,,EMULATE Intel (R) Xeon (R) Manageability capable Processor
ProcEmulation.name: Processor Emulation
ProcEmulation.help_text: This gives the option to emulate different Intel ME FW behavior by changing the processor type on pre-production silicon. This field has no effect on production silicon.

OemTag.name: OEM Tag
OemTag.help_text: An OEM identification number to describe the flash image represented by the value.

HideFwUpdCtrl.name: Hide FW Update Control
HideFwUpdCtrl.help_text: Setting this parameter to 'true' will not allow end users to 'disable' or 'password protect' the ME FW Update mechanism

DbgSiFeat.name: Debug Si Features
DbgSiFeat.help_text: Allows OEM control to enable FW features to assist with debug of the platform. This control has no effect if used on production silicon.

ProdSiFeat.name: Prod Si Features
ProdSiFeat.help_text: Allows OEM control to enable FW features to assist with production of the platform.

AutoBist.name: M3 Autotest Enabled
AutoBist.help_text: This enables ME M3 auto test during platform early boot.

IfrEnabled.name: Independent Firmware Recovery Enable
IfrEnabled.help_text: This allows firmware to be updated via locally installed agent software.

BiosSecureBoot.name: Enable Enforce Secure Boot over IDER
BiosSecureBoot.help_text: false = Disabled, true = Enabled. Enabling this option will advertise support for the enforcement of Secure Boot Over IDER capability as provided by the BIOS.

PrivacySecurityLevel.name: Privacy/Security Level
PrivacySecurityLevel.help_text: Configures ME redirection ports. Default - enables Client Control mode, enables all ports and RCFG, Enhanced - enables Client Control mode, RCFG and requires user consent for redirection, Extreme - disables Client Control mode, RCFG and disables redirection

MeIdleTimeout.name: AMT Idle Timeout
MeIdleTimeout.help_text: Set ME Remote Wake on LAN time out. Valid values are 1-65535.

MngFullPerm.name: Enable Intel (R) Standard Manageability; Disable Intel (R) AMT

ManageAppPerm.name: Manageability Application Permanently Disabled?
ManageAppPerm.help_text: Setting this to Yes permanently disables all manageability application features.

PavPerm.name: PAVP Permanently Disabled?
PavPerm.help_text: Select whether Protected Audio Video Path (PAVP) is permanently disabled.

KvmPerm.name: KVM Permanently Disabled?
KvmPerm.help_text: Select whether KVM is permanently disabled.

TlsPerm.name: TLS Permanently Disabled?
TlsPerm.help_text: Select whether TLS is permanently disabled.

ATPerm.name: Intel (R) Anti-Theft Technology Permanently Disabled?
ATPerm.help_text: Select whether Intel (R) Anti-Theft Technology is permanently disabled.

MeNetworkService.name: Intel (R) ME Network Service Permanently Disabled?
MeNetworkService.help_text: Select whether Intel (R) ME Network Service is permanently disabled.

ManageAppShipState.name: Manageability Application Enable/Disable
ManageAppShipState.help_text: Select whether or not Manageability Application is enabled or disabled.

fTpmShipState.name: Intel (R) Platform Trust Technology Enable/Disable
fTpmShipState.help_text: This enables Intel (R) Platform Trust Technology if the corresponding softstrap is enabled and Enable Intel (R) Platform Trust Technology is enabled.

NfcActive.name: Near Field Communication Enabled
NfcActive.help_text: This setting determines whether Near Field Communication is enabled.

NfcSlaveAddress.name: SMBus Address
NfcSlaveAddress.help_text: This SMBus address should match the SMBus Address on the NFC hardware device.

NfcAlertGpio.name: Active GPIO
NfcAlertGpio.help_text: This setting determines the GPIO NFC will use.

UpgrdSrvcOdmId.name: ODM ID used by Intel (R) Services
UpgrdSrvcOdmId.help_text: ID generated by or registered with Intel (R) Services web servers in order to identify the ODM/Board builder. First of three IDs stored in flash and accessible through Intel (R) MEI interface.

UpgrdSrvcSysIntId.name: System Integrator ID used by Intel (R) Services
UpgrdSrvcSysIntId.help_text: ID generated by or registered with Intel (R) Services web servers in order to identify the System Integrator. Second of three IDs stored in flash and accessible through Intel (R) MEI interface.

UpgrdSrvcRsvdId.name: Reserved ID used by Intel (R) Services
UpgrdSrvcRsvdId.help_text: Reserved ID may be used for a Reseller ID or other Intel (R) Services IDs in the future.

MctpStaticEid0.name: MCTP Static EIDs
MctpStaticEid0.help_text: Defines the ME's 8-bits MCTP Endpoint IDs for each SMBus physical interface (SMBus, SMLink0 and SMLink1). These values are needed for FW to communicate with MCTP end points. For each of these 3 bytes, a value of 0x00 means not used, and values 0xFF or 0x01 - 0x07 or 0x20 - 0x2F are not allowed.

MctpStaticEid1.name: MCTP Static EIDs
MctpStaticEid1.help_text: Defines the ME's 8-bits MCTP Endpoint IDs for each SMBus physical interface (SMBus, SMLink0 and SMLink1). These values are needed for FW to communicate with MCTP end points. For each of these 3 bytes, a value of 0x00 means not used, and values 0xFF or 0x01 - 0x07 or 0x20 - 0x2F are not allowed.

MctpStaticEid2.name: MCTP Static EIDs
MctpStaticEid2.help_text: Defines the ME's 8-bits MCTP Endpoint IDs for each SMBus physical interface (SMBus, SMLink0 and SMLink1). These values are needed for FW to communicate with MCTP end points. For each of these 3 bytes, a value of 0x00 means not used, and values 0xFF or 0x01 - 0x07 or 0x20 - 0x2F are not allowed.

PermitTimerResolution.name: Permit Period Timer Resolution
PermitTimerResolution.help_text: This setting determines what the permit period timer resolution will be.

PkiDnsSuffix.name: PKI DNS Suffix
PkiDnsSuffix.help_text: Set PKI DNS Suffix in dotted string format.

EhbcEnabled.name: Embedded Host Based Configuration
EhbcEnabled.help_text: Embedded Host Based Configuration Enabled. If this is set to true, then Privacy/Security Level will be read-only and set to Default. If Privacy/Security Level is set to non-Default, then this setting will be read-only and set to false.

AllowUnsignedAssertStolen.name: Allow Unsigned Assert Stolen
AllowUnsignedAssertStolen.help_text: true = Unsigned Assert Stolen is enabled. false = The Unsigned Assert Stolen is disabled.

ATBiosRcvryTimer.name: Intel (R) Anti-Theft BIOS Recovery Timer
ATBiosRcvryTimer.help_text: This timer will enable a stolen platform a 30 minute window to allow a FW/BIOS reflash before the system is powered down.

ATFpopHard.value_list: Always Allowed,,Allowed When AT Not Provisioned
ATFpopHard.name: Flash Protection Override Policy Hard
ATFpopHard.help_text: Indicates under which AT conditions it is allowed for ME to enter disabled state to allow full SPI device re-flashing when the HMRFPO is set.

ATFpopSoft.value_list: Always Allowed,,Allowed When AT Not Provisioned
ATFpopSoft.name: Flash Protection Override Policy Soft
ATFpopSoft.help_text: Indicates under which AT conditions it is allowed for ME to enter disabled state via BIOS based MEI messages and allow ME only region re-flash.

PublicKeyHash.name: OEM Public Key Hash
PublicKeyHash.help_text: Enter raw hash string or certificate file. This is a 256-bit field represents the SHA-256 hash of OEM public key corresponding to the private key used to sign the BIOS-SM.

KeyManifestId.name: Key Manifest ID
KeyManifestId.help_text: Contains the hash of another public key, used by the ACM to verify the Boot Policy Manifest.

BGProfile.value_list: Boot Guard Profile 0 - No_FVME,,Boot Guard Profile 1 - VE,,Boot Guard Profile 2 - VME,,Boot Guard Profile 3 - VM,,Boot Guard Profile 4 - FVE,,Boot Guard Profile 5 - FVME
BGProfile.name: Boot Guard Profile Configuration

FBGAcmEn.name: Force Boot Guard ACM Enabled
FBGAcmEn.help_text: false = Disables the Boot Guard ACM to launch during platform boot; true = Force the Boot Guard ACM to launch during platform boot.

ProtectBiosEnvironment.name: Protect BIOS Environment Enabled
ProtectBiosEnvironment.help_text: false = Take no actions to control the environment during execution of BIOS components; true = Controls the environment during execution of BIOS components.

MeasuredBoot.name: Measured Boot Enabled
MeasuredBoot.help_text: false = Platform does not perform measured boot; true = Platform performs measured boot.

VerifiedBoot.name: Verified Boot Enabled
VerifiedBoot.help_text: false = Platform does not perform verified boot; true = Platform performs verified boot.

CpuDebugDis.name: CPU Debug Disabled
CpuDebugDis.help_text: false: do not disable any CPU debug modes. true: disable CPU debug modes.

BspInitDis.name: BSP Initialization Disabled
BspInitDis.help_text: false: if BSP receives an INIT, BSP handles it normally. true: if BST receives an INIT, BST signals an error to the BSS register and enters unrecoverable shutdown.

PttFpfEnable.name: Intel PTT HW Enable/Disable
PttFpfEnable.help_text: Enabled: PTT FPF setting set to enabled. Setting is committed at EOM. Disabled: PTT FPF setting set to disabled. Setting is commited at EOM.

LoggingInt.name: Logging Interface
LoggingInt.help_text: Set the logging interface to the interface to be used or disabled to have no logging interface. WARNING: Changing this setting (by hitting OK in the UI) will reset the Event Filters! They will be set to the default event filter settings for the chosen logging interface.

BufferSize.name: Buffer Size
BufferSize.help_text: Set the buffer size 0-32. Only when logging is set to disabled can this be set to 0.

MacAddr.name: Destination MAC Address
MacAddr.help_text: Enter a MAC Address for the destination
